%N A393949 Decimal expansion of Sum_{p prime} 1/(p*(p+2)) * Product_{p prime} ((1-1/p)^2 * Product_{k>=0} (1 + 2/p^(2^k))).
%C A393949 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is prime.
%F A393949 Equals A185380 * A393948.
%e A393949 0.193337685331885254963810502573364166897551241064085...
%o A393949 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat((1 - 1/p)^2 * prod(k = 0, m, 1 + 2/p^(2^k)));
%o A393949 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); sumeulerrat(1/(p*(p+2))) * c2}
%Y A393949 Cf. A077609, A185380.
%Y A393949 Analogous constants: A222056, A393898.
%Y A393949 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is: A065472 (square), A393948 (1), this constant (prime), A393950 (squarefree), A393951 (Fermi-Dirac prime), A393952 (exponentially 2^n-number), A393953 (4th power).
